          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-1" n="1">When foes are overcome, we preserve them for slaughter,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-2" n="2">To be Hewers of <hi rend="italics">wood</hi> and drawers of water,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-3" n="3">Now although to draw water is not very Good,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-4" n="4">Yet we all should rejoice to be Hewers of <hi rend="italics">Wood</hi>,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-5" n="5">I own it hath often provok'd me to mutter,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-6" n="6">That a rogue so obscure should make such a Clutter.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-7" n="7">But antient Philosophers wisely remark,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-8" n="8">That old rotten <hi rend="italics">wood</hi> will shine in \<hi rend="italics">add</hi>·the\ dark.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-9" n="9">The Heathens \<hi rend="italics">add</hi>·we read\ had Gods made of <hi rend="italics">Wood</hi>,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-10" n="10">Which could do them no harm, if they did them no good,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-11" n="11">But \<hi rend="italics">add</hi>·this\ idol <hi rend="italics">Wood</hi> may do us much evil,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-12" n="12">Their Gods were of <hi rend="italics">Wood</hi>, but our <hi rend="italics">wood</hi> is y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Devil.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-13" n="13">To cut down fine <hi rend="italics">Wood</hi> is a very bad thing,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-14" n="14">And Yet we al know how much it will bring.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-15" n="15">Then if Cutting down <hi rend="italics">wood</hi> brings money Good store,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-16" n="16">Our Money to keep Let us cut down one more;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-17" n="17">Now hear an old tale there antiently Stood</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-18" n="18">I forget in what church an Image \<hi rend="italics">add</hi>·of\ <hi rend="italics">Wood</hi>.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-19" n="19">Concerning this Image there went a prediction,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-20" n="20">It could burn a whole forest, nor was it a fiction,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-21" n="21">'Twas Cut into faggots &amp; put \<hi rend="italics">del</hi>·in\ to y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> flame,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-22" n="22">To burn an old fryar, one \F·<hi rend="italics">overwriting</hi>·f\orest by name,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-23" n="23">My tale is a wise one if well understood,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-24" n="24">Find you but y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Fryar, and I'le find y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> <hi rend="italics">Wood</hi>.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-25" n="25">Some say among Scholars there is a great doubt</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-26" n="26">From what kind of <hi rend="italics">Wood</hi> this tree is cut out,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-27" n="27">Teague made a good pun with a brogue in his Speech,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-28" n="28">And said by my Shoul he's a son of a beech.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-29" n="29">Some call him, a thorn y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Curse of y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Nation,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-30" n="30">As Thorns were design\<hi rend="italics">del</hi>·e·<hi rend="italics">add</hi>·'\d to be from y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Creation.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-31" n="31">Some think 'twas cut out of Poisonous Yew,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-32" n="32">Beneath \<hi rend="italics">del</hi>·t·<hi rend="italics">add</hi>·w\hose Ill shades a Plant Never Grew.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-33" n="33">Some Say \<hi rend="italics">del</hi>·it·was·<hi rend="italics">add</hi>·'twas\ a burch, although very odd,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-34" n="34">For none but a dunce wou'd come under his rod.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-35" n="35">But I'll tell you y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Secret, &amp; pray do not blab,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-36" n="36">He is an old Stump cut out of a Crab.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-37" n="37">And England hath put this Crab to a hard use</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-38" n="38">To Cudgell our bones &amp; for drink give us verjuice.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-39" n="39">And therefore this witness now justly may Boast,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-40" n="40">That none are more properly knights of y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Post.</l>
