            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-109" n="109">Hear one story more and then I will Stop,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-110" n="110">I dreamt <hi rend="italics">Wood</hi> was told he should dye by a drop.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-111" n="111">So my·thought he resolv'd no liquor to taste,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-112" n="112">For fear y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> first drop might as well be his last.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-113" n="113">But dreams are like Oracles its hard to explain them,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-114" n="114">It prov'd that he dyed of a drop at <note place="foot">·Y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Place of excution at Dublin.</note> Kilmainham.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-115" n="115">I w\<hi rend="italics">del</hi>·e\ak'd with delight, &amp; not without hope,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-116" n="116">Very soon to see <hi rend="italics">Wood</hi> drop down from a rope;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-117" n="117">How we and how he at each other should grin,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-118" n="118">Its kindness to hold a Friend up by y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> chin.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-119" n="119">But hold says y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> herald I cannot agree,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-120" n="120">For Metal upon Metal is false Heraldry.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-121" n="121">Why that may be true, but <hi rend="italics">Wood</hi> upon <hi rend="italics">Wood</hi>,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-172Y-line-122" n="122">I'll maintain by my life is Heraldry Good.</l>
